message.content: Geranium robertianum is a flowering plant species in the family Geraniaceae. It is commonly known as Herb Robert or Red Robin and is native to Europe and Asia. Its leaves are deeply lobed and finely hairy, and its flowers are pink-purple in color with five petals. The stem of the plant is thin and fragile, and may be reddish in color. The texture of its leaves is soft and velvety, and they emit a strong odor when crushed. Geranium robertianum is often found growing as a weed in rocky, disturbed areas and can be used for medicinal purposes as well.
